abstract: CAMBRIDGE, Mass.--"Apathy in Blue," the two-man show that played Tuesday in Cleveland, ran 90 minutes without intermission. It has as much chance of holding its audience as the one that bombed in Philadelphia in 1976.

abstract: PEEKSKILL, N.Y.--As 8-year-old Amy Rowley helped celebrate the birthday of a third-grade classmate at the Furnace Woods School in nearby Cortlandt with donut Munchkins and games, Fran Miller sat close by. Amy is deaf and Miss Miller is her personal sign-language interpreter, assigned to all her academic classes by virtue of a Federal Court of Appeals order last July after four years of legal battling.
